              <span class="close">&times;</span>
              <p><center><h3>Sketch Map: Vestlandsutstillingen</h3></center></p>
              <p>This map shows the site-specific audio works that were made for <em>Vestlandsutstillingen</em>* 2019,
              shown at 6 places in West Norway: Ålesund, Haugesund, Øystese, Stavanger, Førde and Bergen.</p>
              <p><strong>Navigating the map:</strong></p>
              &nbsp;
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Play:</strong> press play on any track you'd like to hear. The finger-marker will show your progress.</li>
                <li><strong>Choices:</strong> when you come to an intersection on the track you're listening to, you can choose to continue on
                  that same track, or take a sidetrack. The intersection will be signaled with a knocking sound. If you don't make a choice, 
                  you'll automatically continue on your current track after 10 seconds.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>*<em><u>Vestlandsutstillingen</u> is an annual, traveling exhibition showcasing artist with a connection to the Vestlandet 
              region in Norway. The exhibition was shown at 6 places in West Norway: Ålesund (KUBE), Haugesund (Haugesund Billedgalleri), Øystese (Kunsthuset Kabuso),
              Stavanger (Kunsthall Stavanger), Førde (Sogn og Fjordane Kunstmuseum) and Bergen (Kunstgarasjen). Based on these places, Huizing created 
              6 site-sensitive audio works. In addition, two performances were made, performed during the exhibition opening in Ålesund and Bergen.
              The performance in Bergen was accompanied by a small artist book.
              <a href="https://www.vestlandsutstillingen.no/en/english-home/">Link to Vestlandsutstillingen´s website</a></em></p>
            </div>
